the bags, which bore a caricature of a child with slanted eyes and prominent teeth, carry the words ``coolee bag for your purchases of ice cream and frozen foods.''
unskilled asians who worked for u.s. railroad companies in the middle and late 19th century were called ``coolies.''
those kinds of things are just stupid,'' said david fukuzawa, director of american citizens for justice, an asian-american civil rights organization
paul coleman, a spokesman for meadowdale foods, great scott's parent company, said tuesday the bags would be removed from the chain's 24 metropolitan detroit stores
