the strike disrupted classes for more than 6 million students in elementary, secondary and technical schools in most parts of the country, union and education ministry officials said
spain's two largest unions, the socialist-led general workers union and the communist-oriented workers commissions, and three smaller teachers' unions called the strike
workers commissions spokesman javier doz told spanish television the teachers wanted the socialist government to end ``pay discrimination'' against teachers
he said grade school teachers earn an average $930 a month and want $1,170 while secondary and technical school teachers seek to increase their average monthly pay of $1,080 to $1,380
